Package: maestronemeton
Title: Forest Species and Land Cover Classification Using MAESTRO and FLAIR Models
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Pierre", "Obsteta", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "pierre.obsteta@example.com")
Description: Automatic recognition of forest tree species (13 PureForest classes)
    and land cover classification (19 CoSIA classes) from an area of interest (AOI)
    using MAESTRO and FLAIR models from IGNF (Hugging Face). Downloads orthophotos
    (RGB, IRC) and DEM data from the IGN Geoplateforme via WMS-R. Optionally
    downloads Sentinel-2 (10 spectral bands) and Sentinel-1 (VV+VH radar) via the
    Copernicus Data Space STAC API. MAESTRO pipeline classifies forest species per
    patch using a Vision Transformer (ViT/MAE) with up to 6 modalities (aerial,
    DEM, S2, S1 ascending, S1 descending). FLAIR pipeline performs pixel-level
    semantic segmentation using UNet/UPerNet architectures with Hann window
    blending. Includes spectral indices (NDVI, GNDVI, SAVI) and evaluation
    metrics (mIoU).
